#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:1
msgid "File collection and discovery"
msgstr "檔案收集與探索"

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:3
msgid ""
"You can directly pass _Black_ files, but you can also pass directories and "
"_Black_ will walk them, collecting files to format. It determines what files "
"to format or skip automatically using the inclusion and exclusion regexes "
"and as well their modification time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:8
msgid "Ignoring unmodified files"
msgstr "忽略未修改的檔案"

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:10
msgid ""
"_Black_ remembers files it has already formatted, unless the `--diff` flag "
"is used or code is passed via standard input. This information is stored per-"
"user. The exact location of the file depends on the _Black_ version and the "
"system on which _Black_ is run. The file is non-portable. The standard "
"location on common operating systems is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:15
msgid ""
"Windows: `C:"
"\\Users\\<username>\\AppData\\Local\\black\\black\\Cache\\<version>\\cache."
"<line-length>.<file-mode>.pickle`"
msgstr ""
"Windows：`C:"
"\\Users\\<username>\\AppData\\Local\\black\\black\\Cache\\<version>\\cache."
"<line-length>.<file-mode>.pickle`"

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:17
msgid ""
"macOS: `/Users/<username>/Library/Caches/black/<version>/cache.<line-length>."
"<file-mode>.pickle`"
msgstr ""
"macOS：`/Users/<username>/Library/Caches/black/<version>/cache.<line-length>."
"<file-mode>.pickle`"

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:19
msgid ""
"Linux: `/home/<username>/.cache/black/<version>/cache.<line-length>.<file-"
"mode>.pickle`"
msgstr ""
"Linux：`/home/<username>/.cache/black/<version>/cache.<line-length>.<file-"
"mode>.pickle`"

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:22
msgid ""
"`file-mode` is an int flag that determines whether the file was formatted as "
"3.6+ only, as .pyi, and whether string normalization was omitted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:25
msgid ""
"To override the location of these files on all systems, set the environment "
"variable `BLACK_CACHE_DIR` to the preferred location. Alternatively on macOS "
"and Linux, set `XDG_CACHE_HOME` to your preferred location. For example, if "
"you want to put the cache in the directory you're running _Black_ from, set "
"`BLACK_CACHE_DIR=.cache/black`. _Black_ will then write the above files to `."
"cache/black`. Note that `BLACK_CACHE_DIR` will take precedence over "
"`XDG_CACHE_HOME` if both are set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:32
msgid "Disabling the cache with --no-cache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:34
msgid ""
"If you need Black to always perform a fresh analysis and not consult or "
"update the on-disk cache, use the `--no-cache` flag. When provided, Black "
"will neither read from nor write to the per-user cache. This is useful for "
"debugging, for CI runs where you want a deterministic fresh run, or when you "
"suspect cache corruption."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:39
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "範例："

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:41
msgid "python -m black --no-cache ."
msgstr "python -m black --no-cache ."

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:43
msgid ".gitignore"
msgstr ".gitignore"

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:45
msgid ""
"If `--exclude` is not set, _Black_ will automatically ignore files and "
"directories in `.gitignore` file(s), if present."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/file_collection_and_discovery.md:48
msgid ""
"If you want _Black_ to continue using `.gitignore` while also configuring "
"the exclusion rules, please use `--extend-exclude`."
msgstr ""
